(2, 'SWL-57618-22', 'UPDATEDWaterloo Region Housing v Underwood, 2022 CanLII 87352 (ON LTB)', 'https://canlii.ca/t/js2rt', 'English', 2023, 'Metadata:\nDate:	2022-02-02\nFile number:	\nSWL-57618-22\n\nCitation:	Waterloo Region Housing v Underwood, 2022 CanLII 87352 (ON LTB), <https://canlii.ca/t/js2rt>, retrieved on 2023-05-16\nContent:\n\n\n\n \nOrder under Section 78(6)\nResidential Tenancies Act, 2006\n \nFile Number: SWL-57618-22\n \n \n\n\n\nIn the matter\nof:\n\n\nA,\n  49 HOLBORN DRIVE KITCHENER ON N2A2C9\n\n\n \n\n\n\n\nBetween:\n\n\nWaterloo Region\nHousing\n\n\nLandlord\n\n\n\n\n \n\n\n \nand\n\n\n \n\n\n\n\n \n\n\nAmanda Underwood\n\n\nTenant\n\n\n\n \n \n \nWaterloo Region Housing (the\n\'Landlord\') applied for an order to terminate the tenancy and evict Amanda\nUnderwood (the \'Tenant\') and for an order to have the Tenant pay the rent the\nTenant owes because the Tenant failed to meet a condition\nspecified in the order issued by the Board on September 2, 2021 with respect to\napplication SWL-51067-21.\n \nDeterminations:\n \n1.     The order provided that the Landlord could apply to\nthe Board under section 78 of the Residential Tenancies Act, 2006 (the \'Act\')\nwithout notice to the Tenant\nto terminate the tenancy and evict the Tenant if the Tenant\ndid not meet certain condition(s) specified in the\norder.\n \n2.     I find that the Tenant has not met the following\nconditions specified in the order: The Tenant did not pay $607.35 on or before\nJanuary 1, 2022. The Tenant\ndid not pay\n$1016.00 rent on or before\nJanuary 1, 2022.\n \n3.     The previous application included a request for an\norder for the payment of arrears of rent. The resulting\norder required the Tenant to pay rent or some or all of the arrears of rent. Accordingly, in addition to eviction, the Landlord\nis entitled to request an order for the payment of arrears of rent and\ncompensation.\n \n4.     The Tenant was ordered to pay $12,147.00 for rent arrears\nand the costs\nrelated to the Landlord\'s application fee in Order\nSWL-51067-21. The amount that is still owing from that order is $10,928.30 and\nthat amount is included in this order. As a result, the previous order\nSWL-51067-21 is cancelled.\n \n5.     Since the date of the order, the Tenant has failed to pay the full rent that became\nowing .\n\n\n\n\nFile Number: SWL-57618-22\n \nIt is\nordered that:\n \n1.     Order SWL-51067-21 is cancelled.\n \n2.     The tenancy between\nthe Landlord and the Tenant\nis terminated. The Tenant must move\nout of the rental unit on or before February 13, 2022.\n \n3.     The Tenant shall pay to the Landlord $12,011.11*.(less\nany amount that has been paid since the application was filed on January 19, 2022.)This amount represents\nthe rent owing up to February 2, 2022 and the costs related to the application fee for the previous\napplication.\n \n4.     The Tenant shall\nalso pay to the Landlord\n$33.40 per day for compensation for the use of\nthe unit starting February 3, 2022 to the date the Tenant moves out of the\nunit.\n \n5.     If the Tenant does not pay the Landlord the full amount\nowing* on or before February\n13, 2022, the Tenant will start to owe interest. This will be simple\ninterest calculated from February 14, 2022 at 2.00% annually on the balance\noutstanding.\n \n6.     If the unit is not vacated on or before\nFebruary 13, 2022, then starting\nFebruary 14, 2022, the Landlord may file this order\nwith the Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) so that the eviction may be\nenforced.\n \n7.     Upon receipt of this order,\nthe Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) is directed to give\nvacant possession of the unit to the Landlord on or after February 14, 2022.\n \n \nFebruary 2, 2022\nDate Issued                                                                      Emile Ramlochan\nMember, Landlord\nand Tenant Board\n \nSouth West-RO\n150 Dufferin\nAvenue, Suite 400, 4th Floor London ON N6A5N6\n \nThe tenant has until February 12, 2022\nto file a motion with the Board to set aside the order under\ns. 78(9) of the Act. If the tenant files the motion by February 12, 2022 the order will be stayed and the Board will schedule a hearing.\n \nIf you have any questions about\nthis order, call 416-645-8080 or toll free at 1-888-332-3234.\n \nIn accordance with section 81 of\nthe Act, the part of this order relating to the eviction expires on August 14, 2022 if the order has not been filed on or before this date with the Court Enforcement\nOffice (Sheriff) that has territorial jurisdiction where the rental unit is\nlocated.\n \n*           Refer to the attached Summary\nof Calculations.\n\n\n\n\nSummary of Calculations\nFile Number: SWL-57618-22\n \nAmount the Tenant must pay\n \n\n\n\nReason for amount\nowing\n\n\nPeriod\n\n\nAmount\n\n\n\n\n \nAmount owing\nfrom previous order\nor settlement plus New\n  Arrears and New NSF cheque charges and related administration charges\n\n\n \n$12,011.11\n\n\n\n\n \nLess the rent\n  deposit:\n\n\n \n\n\n \n-$0.00\n\n\n\n\n \nLess the interest owing on the rent deposit\n\n\n \n\n\n \n-$0.00\n\n\n\n\n \nPlus daily\ncompensation owing for\neach day of occupation\n  starting February 3, 2022\n\n\n \n$33.40\n(per day)\n\n\n\n\n \nTotal the Tenant\nmust pay the Landlord:\n\n\n \n$12,011.11, + $33.40\nper day starting February\n  3, 2022', 'Metadata:\nDate:	2022-02-02\nFile number:	\nSWL-57618-22\n\nCitation:	Waterloo Region Housing v Underwood, 2022 CanLII 87352 (ON LTB), <https://canlii.ca/t/js2rt>, retrieved on 2023-05-16\nContent:\n\nOrder under Section 78(6)\nResidential Tenancies Act, 2006\n\nFile Number: SWL-57618-22\n\nIn the matter\nof:\n\nA,\n  49 HOLBORN DRIVE KITCHENER ON N2A2C9\n\nBetween:\n\nWaterloo Region\nHousing\n\nLandlord\n\nand\n\nAmanda Underwood\n\nTenant\n\nWaterloo Region Housing (the\n\'Landlord\') applied for an order to terminate the tenancy and evict Amanda\nUnderwood (the \'Tenant\') and for an order to have the Tenant pay the rent the\nTenant owe