(5, 'CEL-04413-22', 'Grey Bruce Property Rentals Inc v Thompson, 2022 CanLII 70637 (ON LTB)', 'https://canlii.ca/t/jr90z', 'English', 2022, 'Metadata:\nDate:	2022-01-19\nFile number:	\nCEL-04413-22\n\nCitation:	Grey Bruce Property Rentals Inc v Thompson, 2022 CanLII 70637 (ON LTB), <https://canlii.ca/t/jr90z>, retrieved on 2023-05-16\nContent:\n\n\n\n \nOrder under Section 78(6)\nResidential Tenancies Act, 2006\n \nFile Number: CEL-04413-22\n \n \n\n\n\nIn the\n  matter of:\n\n\nUNIT 308,\n1935 9TH AVENUE\nEAST OWEN SOUND ON N4K6B6\n\n\n \n\n\n\n\nBetween:\n\n\nGrey Bruce\nProperty Rentals Inc\n\n\nLandlord\n\n\n\n\n \n\n\n \nand\n\n\n \n\n\n\n\n \n\n\nBrian Thompson\n\n\nTenant\n\n\n\n \n \n \nGrey Bruce Property Rentals\nInc (the \'Landlord\') applied for an order to terminate the tenancy and evict Brian Thompson (the \'Tenant\')\nand for an order to have the Tenant pay the rent the Tenant owes because the\nTenant failed to meet a condition specified in the order issued by the Board on December 15, 2021 with respect to\napplication CEL-02301-21.\n \nDeterminations:\n \n1.     The order provided that the Landlord could apply to\nthe Board under section 78 of the Residential Tenancies Act, 2006 (the \'Act\') without notice\nto the Tenant to terminate\nthe tenancy and evict the\nTenant if the Tenant did not\nmeet certain condition(s) specified\nin the order.\n \n2.     I find that the Tenant has not met the following condition\nspecified in the order: The Tenant did not pay $1,113.20 rent\non or before January 1, 2022.\n \n3.     The previous application included a request for an\norder for the payment of arrears of rent. The resulting order required the Tenant to pay rent or some or all of the arrears of rent. Accordingly, in addition to eviction, the Landlord is\nentitled to request an order for the payment of arrears of rent and\ncompensation.\n \n4.    \nThe Tenant was ordered to pay\n$6,756.00 for rent arrears and the costs related to the Landlord\'s application fee in Order CEL-02301-21. The amount that is still\nowing from that order is $6,756.00 and that amount\nis included in this order. As a result, the previous order CEL-02301-21 is\ncancelled.\n \n5.     Since the date of the order, the Tenant has failed to pay the full rent that became\nowing for the period from January 01, 2022 to January 31, 2022.\n\n\n\n\n \n6.    \nThe Landlord collected a rent deposit\nof $1,100.00 from the Tenant and this deposit is still\nbeing held by the Landlord.\n \n7.     Interest on the rent deposit\nis owing to the Tenant\nfor the period from December\n19, 2020 to January 19, 2022.\n \n \n \nIt is ordered that:\n \n \n1.    \nOrder CEL-02301-21 is cancelled.\n \n2.     The tenancy between\nthe Landlord and the Tenant\nis terminated. The Tenant must move\nout of the rental unit on or before January 30, 2022.\n \n3.     The Tenant shall pay to the Landlord $5,768.10*. (less\nany amount paid since the application was filed on January 7, 2022.)This amount\nrepresents the rent owing up to January 19, 2022 and the costs related\nto the application fee for the previous\napplication, less the rent deposit and interest the Landlord owes on the\nrent deposit.\n \n4.     The Tenant shall also pay to the Landlord $36.60 per day for compensation for the use of\nthe unit starting January 20, 2022 to the date the Tenant moves out of the\nunit.\n \n5.    \nIf the Tenant does not pay the Landlord\nthe full amount owing* on or before\nJanuary 30, 2022, the Tenant\nwill start to owe interest. This will be simple interest calculated from\nJanuary 31, 2022 at 2.00% annually on the balance outstanding.\n \n6.     If the unit is not vacated on or before January 30, 2022, then starting January\n31, 2022, the Landlord may\nfile this order with the Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) so that the\neviction may be enforced.\n \n7.     Upon receipt of this order,\nthe Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) is directed to give\nvacant possession of the unit to the Landlord on or after January 31, 2022.\n \n \nJanuary 19, 2022\n\nDate Issued                                                                      Vladislav Shustov\nMember, Landlord and Tenant Board\n \nCentral-RO\n3 Robert Speck Pkwy,\n5th Floor Mississauga ON\nL4Z2G5\n \nThe tenant has until January 29, 2022 to file a motion with the Board\nto set aside the order\nunder\ns. 78(9) of the Act. If the tenant\nfiles the motion\nby January 29, 2022 the order will be stayed\nand the Board will schedule a hearing.\n\n\n\n\n \nIf you have any questions about this order,\ncall 416-645-8080 or toll free at 1-888-332-3234.\n \nIn accordance with section\n81 of the Act, the part of this order relating to the eviction\nexpires on July 31, 2022 if\nthe order has not been filed on or before this date with the Court Enforcement\nOffice (Sheriff) that has territorial jurisdiction where the rental unit is\nlocated.\n \n*           Refer to the attached Summary\nof Calculations.\n\n\n\n\nSummary of Calculations\nFile Number: CEL-04413-22\n \nAmount the Tenant must pay\n \n\n\n\nReason for amount\nowing\n\n\nPeriod\n\n\nAmount\n\n\n\n\n \nAmount owing\nfrom previous order\nor settlement plus\nNew Arrears and New NSF cheque charges and related administration\n  charges\n\n\n \n$6,869.20\n\n\n\n\n \nLess the rent\n  deposit:\n\n\n \n\n\n \n-$1,100.00\n\n\n\n\n \nLess the interest owing on the rent deposit\n\n\n \nDecember 19, 2020\nto January\n19, 2022\n\n\n \n-$1.10\n\n\n\n\n \nPlus daily\ncompensation owing for each day of occupation starting January 20, 2022\n\n\n \n$36.60\n(per day)\n\n\n\n\n \nTotal the Tenant\nmust pay the Landlord:\n\n\n \n$5,768.10, + $36.60\nper day starting January\n  20, 2022', 'Metadata:\nDate:	2022-01-19\nFile number:	\nCEL-04413-22\n\nCitation:	Grey Bruce Property Rentals Inc v Thompson, 2022 CanLII 70637 (ON LTB), <https://canlii.ca/t/jr90z>, retrieved on 2023-05-16\nContent:\n\nOrder under Section 78(6)\nResidential Tenancies Act, 2006\n\nFile Number: CEL-