 store\nor accumulate any bicycle parts,\ntools, or equipment incidental to bicycle repair,\nor any bicycles that are not for his personal use as described in paragraph 2,\nabove, on the residential property.\n \n5. The Tenant shall not store any\ndiscarded items intended for disposal or which have no practical use on the residential property\nbut shall properly\ndispose of these items within 7 days in accordance by\nthe methods required by municipal bylaws.\n\n\n\n\n \n \n \n \n4.    \nThe Tenant was ordered to pay\n$175.00 for and the costs related to the Landlord\'s application fee in Order\nEAL-88183-20. The amount\nthat is still owing from that order\nis\n$175.00 and that amount is\nincluded in this order. As a result,\nthe previous order EAL-\n88183-20 is cancelled.\n \nIt is ordered that:\n \n1.     Order EAL-88183-20 is cancelled.\n \n2.     The tenancy between\nthe Landlord and the Tenant\nis terminated. The Tenant must move\nout of the rental unit on or before March 1, 2022.\n \n3.    \nThe Tenant shall pay to the Landlord $175.00.\nThis amount represents the costs related to the application fee for the\nprevious application that have not been paid.\n \n4.     The Tenant shall also pay to the Landlord $23.67 per day for compensation for the use of\nthe unit starting February 19, 2022 to the date the Tenant moves out of the\nunit.\n \n5.     If the Tenant does not pay the Landlord the full\namount owing on or before March 1, 2022, the Tenant\nwill start to owe interest. This will be simple interest\ncalculated from March 2, 2022\nat 2.00% annually on the balance outstanding.\n \n6.    \nIf the unit is not vacated\non or before March 1, 2022, then starting March 2, 2022, the\nLandlord may file this order with the Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) so\nthat the eviction may be enforced.\n \n7.     \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n \n \nIan Speers\n\n\n\n\n \n\n\nUpon receipt of this order,\nthe Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) is directed to give\nvacant possession of the u