e full\namount owing on or before March 1, 2022, the Tenant\nwill start to owe interest. This will be simple interest\ncalculated from March 2, 2022\nat 2.00% annually on the balance outstanding.\n\n6.    \nIf the unit is not vacated\non or before March 1, 2022, then starting March 2, 2022, the\nLandlord may file this order with the Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) so\nthat the eviction may be enforced.\n\n7.\n\nIan Speers\n\nUpon receipt of this order,\nthe Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) is directed to give\nvacant possession of the unit to the Landlord on or after March 2, 2022.\n\nFebruary 18, 2022\nDate Issued\nVice Chair, Landlord and Tenant Board\n\nEastern-RO\n255 Albert Street, 4th Floor\nOttawa ON K1P6A9\n\nThe tenant has until February\n28, 2022 to file a motion with the Board to set aside the order\nunder s. 78(9) of the Act. If the tenant files the motion by February 28, 2022\nthe order will be stayed and the Board will schedule a hearing.\n\nIf you have any questions about\nthis order, call 416-645-8080 or toll free at 1-888-332-3234.\n\nIn accordance with section\n81 of the Act, the part of this order\nrelating to the eviction expires\non September 2, 2022 if the order has not been filed on or before this\ndate with the Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) that has territorial\njurisdiction where the rental unit is located.', 'Metadata:\nDate: 2022-02-18\nFile number:\nEAL-99288-22\nCitation: Frankware Inc v Mundell, 2022 CanLII 100252 (ON LTB), <https://canlii.ca/t/jspsg>, retrieved on 2023-05-16\nContent:\nOrder under Section 78(6)\nResidential Tenancies Act, 2006\nFile Number: EAL-99288-22\nIn the matter\nof:\n7 BARTHOLOMEW STREET BROCKVILLE ON K6V2R2\nBetween:\nFrankware\nInc\nLandlord\nand\nWilliam Mundell\nTenant\nFrankware Inc (the \'Landlord\')\napplied for an order to terminate the tenancy and evict William Mundell (the \'Tenant\') and for an order to have the Tenant pay the rent the Tenant owes because the Tenant failed to meet a conditio