(19, 'TEL-21387-22', 'Capreit Limited Parntership v Warwick, 2022 CanLII 97432 (ON LTB)', 'https://canlii.ca/t/jsjm9', 'English', 2022, 'Metadata:\nDate:	2022-02-08\nFile number:	\nTEL-21387-22\n\nCitation:	Capreit Limited Parntership v Warwick, 2022 CanLII 97432 (ON LTB), <https://canlii.ca/t/jsjm9>, retrieved on 2023-05-16\nContent:\n\n\n\n \nOrder under Section 78(6)\nResidential Tenancies Act, 2006\n \nFile Number: TEL-21387-22\n \n \n\n\n\nIn the matter\nof:\n\n\n1708, 100\nWHITE OAKS COURT WHITBY ON L1P1B7\n\n\n \n\n\n\n\nBetween:\n\n\nCapreit Limited Parntership\n\n\nLandlord\n\n\n\n\n \n\n\n \nand\n\n\n \n\n\n\n\n \n\n\nTricia Warwick\n\n\nTenant\n\n\n\n \n \n \nCapreit Limited Parntership (the\n\'Landlord\') applied for an order to terminate the tenancy and evict Tricia\nWarwick (the \'Tenant\') and for an order to have the Tenant pay the rent the\nTenant owes because the Tenant failed to meet a condition\nspecified in the order issued by the Board on November 26, 2021 with respect to\napplication TEL-18755-21.\n \nDeterminations:\n \n1.     The order provided that the Landlord could apply to\nthe Board under section 78 of the Residential Tenancies Act, 2006 (the \'Act\')\nwithout notice to the Tenant\nto terminate the tenancy and evict the Tenant if the Tenant did not meet certain condition(s) specified in the order.\n \n2.     I find that the Tenant has not met the following\nconditions specified in the order: The Tenant did not pay $1419.10 rent on or before January\n1, 2022. The Tenant did not\npay $1000.00 arrears on or before January 20, 2022.\n \n3.     The previous application included a request for an\norder for the payment of arrears of rent. The resulting\norder required the Tenant to pay rent or some or all of the arrears of rent. Accordingly, in addition to eviction, the Landlord\nis entitled to request an order for the payment of arrears of rent and\ncompensation.\n \n4.     The Tenant was ordered to pay $7,397.72 for rent\narrears and the costs related to the Landlord\'s application fee in Order\nTEL-18755-21. The amount\nthat is still owing from that\norder is $6,378.62 and that amount is included in this order. As a result, the\nprevious order TEL-18755-21 is cancelled.\n \n5.     Since the date of the order,\nthe Tenant has failed to pay the full rent that became\nowing for the period from January 1, 2022 to February 28, 2022.\n\n\n\n\n \n6.    \nThe Landlord collected a rent deposit\nof $1,419.10 from the Tenant\nand this deposit\nis still being held by the\nLandlord.\n \n7.    \nInterest on the rent deposit is owing to the Tenant for the period\nfrom May 1, 2020 to February 8, 2022.\n \nIt is ordered that:\n \n1.     Order TEL-18755-21 is cancelled.\n \n2.     The tenancy between\nthe Landlord and the Tenant\nis terminated. The Tenant must move\nout of the rental unit on or before February 19, 2022.\n \n3.     The Tenant shall pay to the Landlord\n$6,350.44*. This amount\nrepresents the rent owing\nup to February 8, 2022 and the costs related to the application fee for the\nprevious application, less the rent deposit and interest the Landlord owes on\nthe rent deposit.\n \n4.     The Tenant shall\nalso pay to the Landlord\n$46.66 per day for compensation for the use of\nthe unit starting February 9, 2022 to the date the Tenant moves out of the\nunit.\n \n5.     If the Tenant does not pay the Landlord the full amount\nowing* on or before February\n19, 2022, the Tenant will start to owe interest. This will be simple\ninterest calculated from February 20, 2022 at 2.00% annually on the balance\noutstanding.\n \n6.    \nIf the unit is not vacated\non or before February 19, 2022, then starting February\n20, 2022, the Landlord may\nfile this order with the Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) so that the\neviction may be enforced.\n \n7.     Upon receipt of this order,\nthe Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) is directed to give\nvacant possession of the unit to the Landlord on or after February 20, 2022.\n \n \nFebruary 8, 2022\nDate Issued                                                                      Emile Ramlochan\nMember, Landlord\nand Tenant Board\n \nToronto East-RO\n2275 Midland Avenue, Unit 2\nToronto ON M1P3E7\n \nThe tenant has until February 18, 2022\nto file a motion with the Board to set aside the order under\ns. 78(9) of the Act. If the tenant files the motion by February 18, 2022 the order will be stayed and the Board will schedule a hearing.\n \nIf you have any questions about\nthis order, call 416-645-8080 or toll free at 1-888-332-3234.\n\n\n\n\n \nIn accordance with section 81 of\nthe Act, the part of this order relating to the eviction expires on August 20, 2022 if the order has not been filed on or before this date with the Court Enforcement\nOffice (Sheriff) that has territorial jurisdiction where the rental unit is\nlocated.\n \n*           Refer to the attached Summary\nof Calculations.\n\n\n\n\nSummary of Calculations\nFile Number: TEL-21387-22\n \nAmount the Tenant must pay\n \n\n\n\nReason for amount\nowing\n\n\nPeriod\n\n\nAmount\n\n\n\n\n \nAmount owing\nfrom previous order\nor settlement plus New\n  Arrears and New NSF cheque charges and related administration charges\n\n\n \n$7,770.96\n\n\n\n\n \nLess the rent\n  deposit:\n\n\n \n\n\n \n-$1,419.10\n\n\n\n\n \nLess the interest owing on the rent deposit\n\n\n \nMay 1, 2020 to February 8,\n2022\n\n\n \n-$1.42\n\n\n\n\n \nPlus daily\ncompensation owing for\neach day of occupation\n  starting February 9, 2022\n\n\n \n$46.66\n(per day)\n\n\n\n\n \nTotal the Tenant\nmust pay the Landlord:\n\n\n \n$6,350.44, + $46.66\nper day starting February\n  9, 2022', 'Metadata:\nDate:	2022-02-08\nFile number:	\nTEL-21387-22\n\nCitation:	Capreit Limited Parntership v Warwick, 2022 CanLII 97432 (ON LTB), <https://canlii.ca/t/jsjm9>, retrieved on 2023-05-16\nContent:\n\nOrder under Section 78(6)\nResidential Tenancies Act, 2006\n\nFile Number: TEL-21387-22\n\nIn the matter\nof:\n\n1708, 100\nWHITE OAK