(26, 'TEL-21399-22', 'Lanmark Management Limited v Mattis, 2022 CanLII 118564 (ON LTB)', 'https://canlii.ca/t/jthm5', 'English', 2022, 'Metadata:\nDate:	2022-02-11\nFile number:	\nTEL-21399-22\n\nCitation:	Lanmark Management Limited v Mattis, 2022 CanLII 118564 (ON LTB), <https://canlii.ca/t/jthm5>, retrieved on 2023-05-16\nContent:\n\n\n\n \nOrder under Section 78(6)\nResidential Tenancies Act, 2006\n \nFile Number: TEL-21399-22\n\n\n\nIn the matter\nof:\n\n\n14, 300 MONTRAVE AVENUE OSHAWA ON L1J4S2\n\n\n \n\n\n\n\nBetween:\n\n\nLanmark Management Limited\n\n\nLandlord\n\n\n\n\n \n\n\n \nand\n\n\n \n\n\n\n\n \n\n\n \nHoward Mattis\n\n\n \nTenant\n\n\n\n \n \nLanmark Management Limited (the \'Landlord\') applied\nfor an order to terminate\nthe tenancy and evict Howard Mattis (the \'Tenant\') and\nfor an order to have the Tenant pay the rent he owes because the Tenant failed\nto meet a condition specified in the order issued by the Board on October 13,\n2021 with respect to application TEL-18405-21.\n \nDeterminations:\n \n1.     The Landlord filed\nthe application more than 30 days after\nthe Tenant failed\nto meet the condition specified in the Order.\n \n2.     Order TEL-18405-21 sets out a payment plan, which\nrequired the Tenant to make payments toward arrears\nand rent over a period\nending November 30, 2021.\nThe Order also included a\nprovision that if the Tenant breached the payment plan, the Landlord could\napply to the Board, under section 78 of the Residential Tenancies Act, 2006\n(the “Act”) for an eviction order without notice to the Tenant.\n \n3.     Subsection 78(5) of the Residential Tenancies Act,\n2006 (the “Act”) requires that any application made under section\n78 be made not later than 30 days after the failure\nof a tenant to meet any such\ncondition in the previous order.\n \n4.     The Landlord filed this L4 Application on January 26,\n2022. In the Declaration that was filed with the application, the Landlord\nstates that contrary to order TEL-18405-21 the Tenant paid $600.00 on October 12, 2021; $400.00\non October 25, 2021; and $650.00 on November 4, 2021.\n \n5.     The problem is that more than 30 days have passed\nsince the date of the last required payment,\nwhich was to take place on November\n25, 2021. Therefore, this L4 Application is statute-barred by\nlimitation.\n \nIt is ordered that:\n \n1.     The Landlord\'s application under section 78 of the Act is dismissed.\n\n\n\n\nFile Number: TEL-21399-22\n \n \n \nFebruary 11, 2022\n\nDate Issued                                                                      Ian Speers\nVice Chair, Landlord and Tenant Board\nToronto East-RO\n2275 Midland Avenue, Unit 2\nToronto ON M1P3E7\n \nIf you have any questions about\nthis order, call 416-645-8080 or toll free at 1-888-332-3234.', 'Metadata:\nDate:	2022-02-11\nFile number:	\nTEL-21399-22\n\nCitation:	Lanmark Management Limited v Mattis, 2022 CanLII 118564 (ON LTB), <https://canlii.ca/t/jthm5>, retrieved on 2023-05-16\nContent:\n\nOrder under Section 78(6)\nResidential Tenancies Act, 2006\n\nFile Number: TEL-21399-22\n\nIn the matter\nof:\n\n14, 300 MONTRAVE AVENUE OSHAWA ON L1J4S2\n\nBetween:\n\nLanmark Management Limited\n\nLandlord\n\nand\n\nHoward Mattis\n\nTenant\n\nLanmark Management Limited (the \'Landlord\') applied\nfor an order to terminate\nthe tenancy and evict Howard Mattis (the \'Tenant\') and\nfor an order to have the Tenant pay the rent he owes because the Tenant failed\nto meet a condition specified in the order issued by the Board on October 13,\n2021 with respect to application TEL-18405-21.\n\nDeterminations:\n\n1.     The Landlord filed\nthe application more than 30 days after\nthe Tenant failed\nto meet the condition specified in the Order.\n\n2.     Order TEL-18405-21 sets out a payment plan, which\nrequired the Tenant to make payments toward arrears\nand rent over a period\nending November 30, 2021.\nThe Order also included a\nprovision that if the Tenant breached the payment p