(35, 'HOL-12841-22', 'Dhiman v Annan, 2022 CanLII 70697 (ON LTB)', 'https://canlii.ca/t/jr92c', 'English', 2022, 'Metadata:\nDate:	2022-01-19\nFile number:	\nHOL-12841-22\n\nCitation:	Dhiman v Annan, 2022 CanLII 70697 (ON LTB), <https://canlii.ca/t/jr92c>, retrieved on 2023-05-16\nContent:\n\n\n\n \n \n\n\n\n \n\n\nOrder under\nSection 78(6)\nResidential Tenancies Act,\n2006\n\n\n \n\n\n\n\n \n\n\nFile Number:\nHOL-12841-22\n\n\n\n\nIn the\nmatter of:\n\n\n27, 3200 SINGLETON AVENUE LONDON ON N6L0C7\n\n\n \n\n\n\n\nBetween:\n\n\nRajeev Dhiman\n\n\nLandlord\n\n\n\n\n \n\n\nand\n\n\n \n\n\n\n\n \n\n\nNathaniel Annan\n\n\nTenant\n\n\n\n \nOn December 29, 2021, Rajeev\nDhiman (the \'Landlord\') applied for an order to terminate the tenancy and evict Nathaniel\nAnnan (the \'Tenant\')\nand for an order to have the Tenant pay the rent the Tenant owes because the Tenant\nfailed to meet a condition specified in the order issued by the Board on\nDecember 24, 2021 with respect to application HOL-10969-21 RV.\n \nDeterminations:\n \n1.    \nThe order provided that the\nLandlord could apply to the Board under section 78 of the Residential Tenancies\nAct, 2006 (the\n\'Act\') without notice\nto the Tenant to terminate\nthe tenancy and evict\nthe Tenant if the Tenant\ndid not meet certain condition(s) specified in the\norder.\n \n2.    \nI\nfind that the Tenant has not met the following\ncondition specified in the order:\n \nThe Tenant\nfailed to pay to the Landlord $1,000.00\non or before December 15, 2021\ntowards December rent, as the cheque tendered by the Tenant was returned for\ninsufficient funds.\n \n3.    \nThe previous application included\na request for an order for the payment of arrears of rent. The resulting order required the Tenant to pay rent or some or all of the arrears of rent. Accordingly, in addition to eviction, the Landlord\nis entitled to request an order for the payment of arrears of rent and\ncompensation.\n \n4.    \nThe Tenant was ordered to pay\n$12,000.00 for rent arrears in Order HOL-10969-21 RV. The amount that is still owing from that order is $12,000.00 and that amount is included\nin this order. As a result, the previous order HOL-10969-21 RV is\ncancelled.\n \n5.    \nThe Landlord collected a rent deposit\nof $1,000.00 from the Tenant and this deposit is still\nbeing held by the Landlord.\n \n6.    \nInterest on the rent deposit is owing to the Tenant for the period from February 20, 2019\nto January 19, 2022.\n\n\n\n\nFile Number: HOL-12841-22\n \n \n \nIt is ordered that:\n \n1.     Order HOL-10969-21 RV is cancelled.\n \n2.     The tenancy between\nthe Landlord and the Tenant\nis terminated. The Tenant must move\nout of the rental unit on or before January 30, 2022.\n \n3.     The Tenant shall pay to the Landlord\n$11,977.00*. This amount\nrepresents the rent owing\nup to December 31, 2021, less the rent deposit and interest the Landlord owes\non the rent deposit.\n \n4.     The Tenant shall also pay to the Landlord $32.88\nper day for compensation for the use of\nthe unit starting January 1, 2022 to the date the Tenant moves out of the unit.\n \n5.     If the Tenant\ndoes not pay the Landlord\nthe full amount\nowing* on or before January\n30, 2022, the Tenant will start to owe interest. This will be simple\ninterest calculated from January 31, 2022 at 2.00% annually on the balance\noutstanding.\n \n6.     If the unit is not vacated on or before\nJanuary 30, 2022, then starting\nJanuary 31, 2022, the Landlord may file this order\nwith the Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) so that the eviction may be\nenforced.\n \n7.     Upon receipt of this order,\nthe Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) is directed to give vacant\npossession of the unit to the Landlord on or after January 31, 2022.\n \n \n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n \nIan Speers\n\n\n\n\n \n\n\nJanuary 19, 2022 Date Issued\nVice Chair, Landlord and Tenant Board\n \nHead Office\n777 Bay Street, 12th Floor\nToronto Ontario M5G2E5\n \nThe tenant has until January 29, 2022 to file a motion with the Board to set aside the order under\ns. 78(9) of the Act. If the tenant files the motion by January 29, 2022 the order will be stayed and\nthe Board will schedule a hearing.\n \nIf you have any questions about\nthis order, call 416-645-8080 or toll free at 1-888-332-3234.\n \nIn accordance with section\n81 of the Act, the part of this order\nrelating to the eviction expires\non July 31, 2022 if the order has not been filed on or before this date\nwith the Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) that has territorial jurisdiction\nwhere the rental unit is located.\n \n*           Refer to the attached Summary\nof Calculations.\n\n\n\n\nSummary of Calculations\nFile Number: HOL-12841-22\n \nAmount the Tenant must pay\n \n\n\n\nReason for amount\nowing\n\n\nPeriod\n\n\nAmount\n\n\n\n\n \nAmount owing from\nprevious order plus\nNew Arrears and New\n  NSF cheque charges and related administration charges\n\n\n \n$13,000.00\n\n\n\n\n \nLess the rent\n  deposit:\n\n\n \n\n\n \n-$1,000.00\n\n\n\n\n \nLess the interest owing on the rent deposit\n\n\n \nFebruary 20, 2019\nto January\n19, 2022\n\n\n \n-$23.00\n\n\n\n\n \nPlus daily compensation owing for each\nday of occupation starting January 1, 2022\n\n\n \n$32.88\n(per day)\n\n\n\n \n \n\n\n\n \nTotal the Tenant\nmust pay the Landlord:\n\n\n \n$11,977.00, + $32.88\nper day starting January 1,\n  2022', 'Metadata:\nDate:	2022-01-19\nFile number:	\nHOL-12841-22\n\nCitation:	Dhiman v Annan, 2022 CanLII 70697 (ON LTB), <https://canlii.ca/t/jr92c>, retrieved on 2023-05-16\nContent:\n\nOrder under\nSection 78(6)\nResidential Tenancies Act,\n2006\n\nFile Number:\nHOL-12841-22\n\nIn the\nmatter of:\n\n27, 3200 SINGLETON AVENUE LONDON ON N6L0C7\n\nBetween:\n\nRajeev Dhiman\n\nLandlord\n\nand\n\nNathaniel Annan\n\nTenant\n\nOn December 29, 2021, Rajeev\nDhiman (the \'Landlord\') applied for an order to terminate the tenancy and evict Nathaniel\nAnnan (the \'Tenant\')\nand for an order to have the Tenant 