(36, 'SOL-26817-22', 'Homestead Land Holdings Limited v Ferris, 2022 CanLII 80866 (ON LTB)', 'https://canlii.ca/t/jrskt', 'English', 2022, 'Metadata:\nDate:	2022-01-26\nFile number:	\nSOL-26817-22\n\nCitation:	Homestead Land Holdings Limited v Ferris, 2022 CanLII 80866 (ON LTB), <https://canlii.ca/t/jrskt>, retrieved on 2023-05-16\nContent:\n\n\n\n \nOrder under Section 78(6)\nResidential Tenancies Act, 2006\n \nFile Number: SOL-26817-22\n \n \n\n\n\nIn the\n  matter of:\n\n\n606, 120 EDINBURGH ROAD\nS GUELPH ON N1H5P7\n\n\n \n\n\n\n\nBetween:\n\n\nHomestead Land Holdings Limited\n\n\nLandlord\n\n\n\n\n \n\n\n \nand\n\n\n \n\n\n\n\n \n\n\nJon Ferris Shawna\nDoyle\n\n\nTenants\n\n\n\n \n \n \nHomestead Land Holdings Limited\n(the \'Landlord\') applied for an order to terminate the tenancy and evict Jon\nFerris and Shawna Doyle (the \'Tenants\') and for an order to have the Tenants pay the rent they owe because the Tenants failed\nto meet a condition specified in the order\nissued by the Board on August\n30, 2021 with respect to application SOL-18110-20.\n \nDeterminations:\n \n1.     The order provided that the Landlord could apply to\nthe Board under section 78 of the Residential Tenancies Act, 2006 (the\n\'Act\') without notice to the Tenants to terminate the tenancy and evict the Tenants if the Tenants\ndid not meet certain condition(s) specified in the\norder.\n \n2.     I find that the Tenants\nhave not met the following\nconditions specified in the order:\nThe Tenant did not pay $1654.08 on or before December 23, 2021.\n \n3.     The previous application included a request for an\norder for the payment of arrears of rent. The resulting\norder required the Tenants to pay rent or some or all of the arrears of rent. Accordingly, in addition to\neviction, the Landlord is entitled to request an order for the payment of\narrears of rent and compensation.\n \n4.    \nThe Tenants were ordered to pay\n$6,654.08 for rent arrears and the costs related to the Landlord\'s application\nfee in Order SOL-18110-20. The amount that is still owing from that order is $1,654.08\nand that amount is included\nin this order.\nAs a result, the previous order SOL-18110-20 is cancelled.\n \n5.     Since the date of the order, the Tenants have failed to pay the full rent that became\nowing for the period from December 1, 2021 to January 31, 2022.\n\n\n\n\n \n6.    \nThe Landlord collected a rent deposit\nof $1,407.25 from the Tenants\nand this deposit\nis still being held by the Landlord.\n \n7.     Interest on the rent deposit\nis owing to the Tenants\nfor the period\nfrom May 1, 2021 to\nJanuary 26, 2022.\n \nIt is ordered that:\n \n1.     Order SOL-18110-20 is cancelled.\n \n2.     The tenancy between\nthe Landlord and the Tenants\nis terminated. The Tenants must move out of the rental unit on or\nbefore February 6, 2022.\n \n3.     The Tenants shall\npay to the Landlord $1,100.24*. This amount represents the rent owing up to January 26, 2022 and the\ncosts related to the application fee for the previous application, less the\nrent deposit and interest the Landlord owes on the rent deposit.\n \n4.     The Tenants shall\nalso pay to the Landlord\n$44.82 per day for compensation for the use of the unit starting January 27, 2022\nto the date the Tenants move out of the unit.\n \n5.    \nIf the Tenants do not pay the Landlord\nthe full amount\nowing* on or before February\n6, 2022, the Tenants\nwill start to owe interest. This will be simple interest\ncalculated from February 7,\n2022 at 2.00% annually on the balance outstanding.\n \n6.    \nIf the unit is not vacated\non or before February 6, 2022, then starting February\n7, 2022, the Landlord may file\nthis order with the Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) so that the eviction may\nbe enforced.\n \n7.    \nUpon receipt of this order,\nthe Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) is directed to give\nvacant possession of the unit to the Landlord on or after February 7, 2022.\n \n \nJanuary 26, 2022\n\nDate Issued                                                                      Vladislav Shustov\nMember, Landlord\nand Tenant Board\n \nSouthern-RO\n119 King Street West, 6th Floor Hamilton ON L8P4Y7\n \nThe tenant has until February 5, 2022 to file a motion with the Board to set aside the order under\ns. 78(9) of the Act. If the tenant\nfiles the motion\nby February 5, 2022 the order will be stayed\nand the Board will schedule a hearing.\n \nIf you have any questions about this order,\ncall 416-645-8080 or toll free at 1-888-332-3234.\n\n\n\n\n \nIn accordance with section 81 of the Act, the part of this order relating to the eviction\nexpires on August 7, 2022 if the order\nhas not been filed on or before\nthis date with the Court Enforcement\nOffice (Sheriff) that has territorial jurisdiction where the rental unit is\nlocated.\n \n*    Refer\nto the attached Summary of Calculations.\n\n\n\n\nSummary of Calculations\nFile Number: SOL-26817-22\n \nAmount the Tenant must pay\n \n\n\n\nReason for amount\nowing\n\n\nPeriod\n\n\nAmount\n\n\n\n\n \nAmount owing\nfrom previous order\nor settlement plus\nNew Arrears and New NSF cheque charges and related administration\n  charges\n\n\n \n$2,507.49\n\n\n\n\n \nLess the rent\n  deposit:\n\n\n \n\n\n \n-$1,407.25\n\n\n\n\n \nLess the interest owing on the rent deposit\n\n\n \nMay 1, 2021\nto January 26,\n2022\n\n\n \n-$0.00\n\n\n\n\n \nPlus daily\ncompensation owing for each day of occupation starting January 27, 2022\n\n\n \n$44.82\n(per day)\n\n\n\n\n \nTotal the Tenants\nmust pay the Landlord:\n\n\n \n$1,100.24, + $44.82\nper day starting January\n  27, 2022', 'Metadata:\nDate:	2022-01-26\nFile number:	\nSOL-26817-22\n\nCitation:	Homestead Land Holdings Limited v Ferris, 2022 CanLII 80866 (ON LTB), <https://canlii.ca/t/jrskt>, retrieved on 2023-05-16\nContent:\n\nOrder under Section 78(6)\nResidential Tenancies Act, 2006\n\nFile Number: SOL-26817-22\n\nIn the\n  matter of:\n\n606, 120 EDINBURGH ROAD\nS GUELPH ON N1H5P7\n\