 owe interest. This will be simple interest\ncalculated from February 7,\n2022 at 2.00% annually on the balance outstanding.\n6.\nIf the unit is not vacated\non or before February 6, 2022, then starting February\n7, 2022, the Landlord may file\nthis order with the Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) so that the eviction may\nbe enforced.\n7.\nUpon receipt of this order,\nthe Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) is directed to give\nvacant possession of the unit to the Landlord on or after February 7, 2022.\nJanuary 26, 2022\nDate Issued                        Vladislav Shustov\nMember, Landlord\nand Tenant Board\nSouthern-RO\n119 King Street West, 6th Floor Hamilton ON L8P4Y7\nThe tenant has until February 5, 2022 to file a motion with the Board to set aside the order under\ns. 78(9) of the Act. If the tenant\nfiles the motion\nby February 5, 2022 the order will be stayed\nand the Board will schedule a hearing.\nIf you have any questions about this order,\ncall 416-645-8080 or toll free at 1-888-332-3234.\nIn accordance with section 81 of the Act, the part of this order relating to the eviction\nexpires on August 7, 2022 if the order\nhas not been filed on or before\nthis date with the Court Enforcement\nOffice (Sheriff) that has territorial jurisdiction where the rental unit is\nlocated.\n*  Refer\nto the attached Summary of Calculations.\nSummary of Calculations\nFile Number: SOL-26817-22\nAmount the Tenant must pay\nReason for amount\nowing\nPeriod\nAmount\nAmount owing\nfrom previous order\nor settlement plus\nNew Arrears and New NSF cheque charges and related administration\ncharges\n$2,507.49\nLess the rent\ndeposit:\n-$1,407.25\nLess the interest owing on the rent deposit\nMay 1, 2021\nto January 26,\n2022\n-$0.00\nPlus daily\ncompensation owing for each day of occupation starting January 27, 2022\n$44.82\n(per day)\nTotal the Tenants\nmust pay the Landlord:\n$1,100.24, + $44.82\nper day starting January\n27, 2022', 'Metadata: Date: 2022-01-26 File number: SOL-26817-22 Citation: Homestead Land Holdings Limited v Ferris, 2022 CanLII 80866 (ON LTB), <https://canlii.ca/t/jrskt>, retrieved on 2023-05-16 Content: Order under Section 78(6) Residential Tenancies Act, 2006 File Number: SOL-26817-22 In the matter of: 606, 120 EDINBURGH ROAD S GUELPH ON N1H5P7 Between: Homestead Land Holdings Limited Landlord and Jon Ferris Shawna Doyle Tenants Homestead Land Holdings Limited (the \'Landlord\') applied for an order to terminate the tenancy and evict Jon Ferris and Shawna Doyle (the \'Tenants\') and for an order to have the Tenants pay the rent they owe because the Tenants failed to meet a condition specified in the order issued by the Board on August 30, 2021 with respect to application SOL-18110-20. Determinations: 1.  The order provided that the Landlord could apply to the Board under section 78 of the Residential Tenancies Act, 2006 (the \'Act\') without notice to the Tenants to terminate the tenancy and evict the Tenants if the Tenants did not meet certain condition(s) specified in the order. 2.  I find that the Tenants have not met the following conditions specified in the order: The Tenant did not pay $1654.08 on or before December 23, 2021. 3.  The previous application included a request for an order for the payment of arrears of rent. The resulting order required the Tenants to pay rent or some or all of the arrears of rent. Accordingly, in addition to eviction, the Landlord is entitled to request an order for the payment of arrears of rent and compensation. 4. The Tenants were ordered to pay $6,654.08 for rent arrears and the costs related to the Landlord\'s application fee in Order SOL-18110-20. The amount that is still owing from that order is $1,654.08 and that amount is included in this order. As a result, the previous order SOL-18110-20 is cancelled. 5.  Since the date of the order, the Tenants have failed to pay the full rent that became owing for the period from December 1, 2021 to January 31, 2022. 6. The Landlord collected a rent deposit of $1,407.25 from the Tenants and this deposit is still being held by the Landlord. 7.  Interest on the rent deposit is owing to the Tenants for the period from May 1, 2021 to January 26, 2022. It is ordered that: 1.  Order SOL-18110-20 is cancelled. 2.  The tenancy between the Landlord and the Tenants is terminated. The Tenants must move out of the rental unit on or before February 6, 2022. 3.  The Tenants shall pay to the Landlord $1,100.24*. This amount represents the rent owing up to January 26, 2022 and the costs related to the application fee for the previous application, less the rent deposit and interest the Landlord owes on the rent deposit. 4.  The Tenants shall also pay to the Landlord $44.82 per day for compensation for the use of the unit starting January 27, 2022 to the date the Tenants move out of the unit. 5. If the Tenants do not pay the Landlord the full amount owing* on or before February 6, 2022, the Tenants will start to owe interest. This will be simple interest calculated from February 7, 2022 at 2.00% annually on the balance outstanding. 6. If the unit is not vacated on or before February 6, 2022, then starting February 7, 2022, the Landlord may file this order with the Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) so that the eviction may be enforced. 7. Upon receipt of this order, the Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) is directed to give vacant possession of the unit to the Landlord on or after February 7, 2022. January 26, 2022 Date Issued                        Vladislav Shustov Member, Landlord and Tenant Board Southern-RO 119 King Street West, 6th Floor Hamilton ON L8P4Y7 The tenant has until February 5, 2022 to file a motion with the Board to set aside the order under s. 78(9) of the Act. If the tenant files the motion by February 5, 2022 the order will be stayed and the Board will schedule a hearing. If you have any questions about this order, call 416-645-8080 or toll free at 1-888-332-3234. In accordance with section 81 of the Act, the part of this order relating to the eviction expires on August 7, 2022 if the order has not been filed on or before this date with the Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) that has territorial jurisdiction where the rental unit is located. *  Refer to the attached Summary of Calculations. Summary of Calculations File Number: SOL-26817-22 Amount the Tenant must pay Reason for amount owing Period Amount Amount owing from previous order or settlement plus New Arrears and New NSF cheque charges and related administration charges $2,507.49 Less the rent deposit: -$1,407.25 Less the interest owing on the rent deposit May 1, 2021 to January 26, 2022 -$0.00 Plus daily compensation owing for each day of occupation starting January 27, 2022 $44.82 (per day) Total the Tenants must pay the Landlord: $1,100.24, + $44.82 per day starting January 27, 2022', 'Date: 2022-01-26 File number: SOL-26817-22  Citation: Homestead Land Holdings Limited v Ferris, 2022 CanLII 80866 (ON LTB), <https://canlii.ca/t/jrskt>, retrieved on 2023-05-16', 'Order under Section 78(6) Residential Tenancies Act, 2006  File Number: SOL-26817-22      In the matter of:   606, 120 EDINBURGH ROAD S GUELPH ON N1H5P7        Between:   Homestead Land Holdings Limited   Landlord         and           Jon Ferris Shawna Doyle   Tenants       Homestead Land Holdings Limited (the \'Landlord\') applied for an order to terminate the tenancy and evict Jon Ferris and Shawna Doyle (the \'Tenants\') and for an order to have the Tenants pay the rent they owe because the Tenants failed to meet a condition specified in the order issued by the Board on August 30, 2021 with respect to application SOL-18110-20.  Determinations:  1. The order provided that the Landlord could apply to the Board under section 78 of the Residential Tenancies Act, 2006 (the \'Act\') without notice to the Tenants to terminate the tenancy and evict the Tenants if the Tenants did not meet certain condition(s) specified in the order.  2. I find that the Tenants have not met the following conditions specified in the order: The Tenant did not pay $1654.08 on or before December 23, 2021.  3. The previous application included a request for an order for the payment of arrears of rent. The resulting order required the Tenants to pay rent or some or all of the arrears of rent. Accordingly, in addition to eviction, the Landlord is entitled to request an order for the payment of arrears of rent and compensation.  4. The Tenants were ordered to pay $6,654.08 for rent arrears and the costs related to the Landlord\'s application fee in Order SOL-18110-20. The amount that is still owing from that order is $1,654.08 and that amount is included in this order. As a result, the previous order SOL-18110-20 is cancelled.  5. Since the date of the order, the Tenants have failed to pay the full rent that became owing for the period from December 1, 2021 to January 31, 2022.      6. The Landlord collected a rent deposit of $1,407.25 from the Tenants and this deposit is still being held by the Landlord.  7. Interest on the rent deposit is owing to the Tenants for the period from May 1, 2021 to January 26, 2022.  It is ordered that:  1. Order SOL-18110-20 is cancelled.  2. The tenancy between the Landlord and the Tenants is terminated. The Tenants must move out of the rental unit on or before February 6, 2022.  3. The Tenants shall pay to the Landlord $1,100.24*. This amount represents the rent owing up to January 26, 2022 and the costs related to the application fee for the previous application, less the rent deposit and interest the Landlord owes on the rent deposit.  4. The Tenants shall also pay to the Landlord $44.82 per day for compensation for the use of the unit starting January 27, 2022 to the date the Tenants move out of the unit.  5. If the Tenants do not pay the Landlord the full amount owing* on or before February 6, 2022, the Tenants will start to owe interest. This will be simple interest calculated from February 7, 2022 at 2.00% annually on the balance outstanding.  6. If the unit is not vacated on or before February 6, 2022, then starting February 7, 2022, the Landlord may file this order with the Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) so that the eviction may be enforced.  7. Upon receipt of this order, the Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) is directed to give vacant possession of the unit to the Landlord on or after February 7, 2022.   January 26, 2022  Date Issued Vladislav Shustov Member, Landlord and Tenant Board  Southern-RO 119 King Street West, 6th Floor Hamilton ON L8P4Y7  The tenant has until February 5, 2022 to file a motion with the Board to set aside the order under s. 78(9) of the Act. If the tenant files the motion by February 5, 2022 the order will be stayed and the Board will schedule a hearing.  If you have any questions about this order, call 416-645-8080 or toll free at 1-888-332-3234.      In accordance with section 81 of the Act, the part of this order relating to the eviction expires on August 7, 2022 if the order has not been filed on or before this date with the Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) that has territorial jurisdiction where the rental unit is located.  * Refer to the attached Summary of Calculations.     Summary of Calculations File Number: SOL-26817-22  Amount the Tenant must pay     Reason for amount owing   Period   Amount      Amount owing from previous order or settlement plus New Arrears and New NSF cheque charges and related administration charges    $2,507.49      Less the rent deposit:       -$1,407.25      Less the interest owing on the rent deposit    May 1, 2021 to January 26, 2022    -$0.00      Plus daily compensation owing for each day of occupation starting January 27, 2022    $44.82 (per day)      Total the Tenants must pay the Landlord:    $1,100.24, + $44.82 per day starting January 27, 2022', '20 Edinburgh Road S Guelph', '', 'December 23, 2021', '', 'January 26, 2022', '', 'Vladislav Shustov', '', '5. Since the date