(40, 'TSL-25998-22', 'Briarlane Rental Property Management In Trust of CMHC v O\'Riordan, 2022 CanLII 86366 (ON LTB)', 'https://canlii.ca/t/js1j6', 'English', 2022, 'Metadata:\nDate:	2022-01-25\nFile number:	\nTSL-25998-22\n\nCitation:	Briarlane Rental Property Management In Trust of CMHC v O\'Riordan, 2022 CanLII 86366 (ON LTB), <https://canlii.ca/t/js1j6>, retrieved on 2023-05-16\nContent:\n\n\n\n \nOrder under Section 78(6)\nResidential Tenancies Act, 2006\n \nFile Number: TSL-25998-22\n \n \nIn the matter of:       1, 2377 DANFORTH\nAVENUE\nTORONTO ON M4C1K8\n \n\n\n\n\nBetween:                  Briarlane Rental\nProperty Management In Trust Of CMHC\n\n\nLandlord\n\n\n\n\n \n \nand\n \n\n\n\n\nChloe O\'Riordan David Hayes\n\n\nTenants\n\n\n\n\n \n \n \nOn January 12, 2022, Briarlane\nRental Property Management In Trust Of CMHC (the \'Landlord\') applied in this L4\napplication for an order to terminate the tenancy and evict David Hayes and\nChloe O\'Riordan (the \'Tenants\') and for an order to have the Tenants pay the\nrent they owe because the Tenants\nfailed to meet a condition\nspecified in the consent order\nissued by the Board\non December 29, 2021 with respect to L1 application TSL-23694-21.\n \nDeterminations:\n \n1.       \nThe previous consent order\nprovided that the Landlord could apply to the Board under section 78 of the Residential Tenancies Act, 2006 (the \'Act\') without notice\nto the Tenants to terminate the tenancy and evict the Tenants if the\nTenants did not meet certain condition(s) specified in the order.\n \n2.       \nI find that the Tenants have not\nmet the following condition specified in the order: The Tenant failed\nto pay the lawful monthly rent, on or before January\n1, 2022. This was\na breach of the consent order. This L4 application was filed within 30 days of\nthe breach.\n \n3.       \nThe previous L1 application included a request\nfor an order for the payment\nof arrears of rent.\nThe resulting order required the Tenants to pay rent or\nsome or all of the arrears of rent. Accordingly, in addition to eviction, in this L4\napplication the Landlord is entitled to request an order for the payment of\narrears of rent and compensation.\n \n4.       \nThe Tenants were ordered to pay\n$6,536.00 for rent arrears and NSF cheque charges and the costs related to the\nLandlord\'s application fee in Order TSL-23694-21. The amount that is still owing from that order\nis $3,536.00 and that amount is included\nin this order. As a result,\nthe previous order TSL-23694-21 is cancelled.\n\n\n\n\n \n5.       \nSince the date of the order,\nthe Tenants have failed to pay the full rent that became\nowing for the period from January 1, 2022 to January 31, 2022.\n \n6.       \nOn December 1, 2017, the Landlord\ncollected a rent deposit of $1,418.00 from the\nTenants and this deposit is still being held by the Landlord.\n \n7.       \nInterest was last paid out to the Tenants\nup to the period ending December, 31, 20202.\nInterest is owing on the rent deposit for the period from January 1, 2021 to\nthis order date, January 25, 2022.\n \nIt is ordered that:\n \n1.       \nThe previous consent order\nTSL-23694-21 is cancelled.\n \n2.       \nThe tenancy between the Landlord and the Tenants\nis terminated. The Tenants must move\nout of the rental\nunit on or before\nFebruary 5, 2022 (standard 11 days from the issuance date of this order).\n \n3.       \nIf the Tenant made any payments\nafter this L4 application was filed, those amounts shall be deducted from the calculations\nbelow.\n \nSee attached Summary\nof Calculations\n \n4.       \nThe Tenants shall pay to the Landlord\n$3,282.31*. This amount represents the rent owing up to January 25, 2022 and the\ncosts related to the application fee for the previous L1 application, less the\nrent deposit and interest the Landlord owes on the rent deposit.\n \n5.       \nThe Tenants shall also pay to the Landlord $46.62 per day for compensation for the use of the unit starting January 26, 2022\nto the date the Tenants actually move out of the rental unit or get evicted.\n \n6.       \nIf the Tenants do not pay the Landlord the full amount\nowing* on or before February\n5, 2022, the Tenants will start\nto owe interest. This will be\nsimple interest calculated from February 6, 2022 at 2.00% annually on the balance\noutstanding.\n \n7.       \nIf the unit is not vacated\non or before February 5, 2022, then starting February\n6, 2022, the Landlord may file\nthis order with the Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) so that the eviction may\nbe enforced.\n \n8.       \nUpon receipt of this order,\nthe Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) is directed to give\nvacant possession of the unit to the Landlord on or after February 6, 2022.\n \n \nJanuary 25, 2022\nDate Issued                                                                      Michelle Tan\nMember,\nLandlord and Tenant Board\n \nToronto South-RO\n\n\n\n\n \n15 Grosvenor Street, 1st Floor\nToronto ON M7A 2G6\n \nThe tenant\nhas until February\n4, 2022 to file a motion with the Board to set aside the order under\ns. 78(9) of the Act. If the tenant files the motion by February 4, 2022 the order will be\nstayed and the Board will schedule a hearing.\n \nIf you have any questions about this order,\ncall 416-645-8080 or toll free at 1-888-332-3234.\n \nIn accordance with section 81 of the Act, the part of this order relating\nto the eviction expires on August\n6, 2022 if the order has not been filed\non or before this date with the Court\nEnforcement Office (Sheriff) that has territorial jurisdiction where the\nrental unit is located.\n\n\n\n\nSummary of Calculations\nFile Number: TSL-25998-22\n \nAmount the Tenant must pay to the Landlord\n \n\n\n\nReason for amount\nowing\n\n\nPeriod\n\n\nAmount\n\n\n\n\n \nAmount owing from previous consent order ($3,536.00\n  up to Dec 31 2021)\nplus New Arrears and New NSF\ncheque charges and related\n  administration charges ($1,165.48 from Jan 1, 2022 pro-rated up to Jan 25,\n  2022)\n\n\n \n$4,701.48\n\n\n\n\n \nLess the rent deposit:\n\n\n \n\n\n \n-$1,418.00\n\n\n\n\n \nLess the interest owing on the rent deposit\n\n\n \nJanuary 1, 2021\nto January\n25, 2022\n\n\n \n-$1.17\n\n\n\n\n \nPlus daily\ncompensation owing for\neach day of occupation\n  starting January 26, 2022\n\n\n \n$46.62\n(per day)', 'Metadata:\nDate:	2022-01-25\nFile number:	\nTSL-25998-22\n\nCitation:	Briarlane Rental Property Management In Trust of CMHC v O\'Riordan, 2022 CanLII 86366 (ON LTB), <https://canlii.ca/t/js1j6>, retrieved on 2023-05-16\nContent:\n\nOrder under Section 78(6)\nResidential Tenancies Act, 2006\n\nFile Number: TSL-25998-22\n\nIn the matter of:       1, 2377 DANFORTH\nAVENUE\nTORONTO ON M4C1K8\n\nBetween:                  Briarlane Rental\nProperty Management In Trust Of CMHC\n\nLandlord\n\nand\n\nChloe O\'Riordan David Hayes\n\nTenants\n\nOn January 12, 2022, Briarlane\nRental Property Management In Trust Of CMHC (the \'Landlord\') applied in this L4\napplication for an order to terminate the tenancy and evict David Hayes and\nChloe O\'Riordan (the \'Tenants\') and for an order to have the Tenants pay the\nrent they owe because the Tenants\nfailed to meet a condition\nspecified in the consent order\nissued by the Board\non December 29, 2021 with respect to L1 application TSL-23694-21.\n\nDeterminations:\n\n1.       \nThe previous consent order\nprovided that the Landlord could apply to the Board under section 78 of the Residential Tenancies Act, 2006 (the \'Act\') without notice\nto the Tenants to terminate the tenancy and evict the Tenants if the\nTenants did not meet certain condition(s) specified in the order.\n\n2.       \nI find that the Tenants have not\nmet the following condition specified in the order: The Tenant failed\nto pay the lawful monthly rent, on or before January\n1, 2022. This was\na breach of the consent order. This L4 application was filed within 30 days of\nthe breach.\n\n3.       \nThe prev