(46, 'TNL-36576-22', 'Nubury Properties Limited v Banos, 2022 CanLII 122571 (ON LTB)', 'https://canlii.ca/t/jtp3j', 'English', 2022, 'Metadata:\nDate:	2022-02-03\nFile number:	\nTNL-36576-22\n\nCitation:	Nubury Properties Limited v Banos, 2022 CanLII 122571 (ON LTB), <https://canlii.ca/t/jtp3j>, retrieved on 2023-05-16\nContent:\n\n\n\n \nOrder under Section 78(6)\nResidential Tenancies Act, 2006\n \nFile Number: TNL-36576-22\n \n \n\n\n\nIn the matter\nof:\n\n\n1713, 377 RIDELLE AVENUE TORONTO ON M6B1K2\n\n\n \n\n\n\n\nBetween:\n\n\nNubury Properties Limited..\n\n\nLandlord\n\n\n\n\n \n\n\n \nand\n\n\n \n\n\n\n\n \n\n\nAdgar J.m. Banos Miriam B. Torres\n\n\nTenants\n\n\n\n \n \n \nOn January 10, 2022, Nubury\nProperties Limited.. (the \'Landlord\') applied for an order to terminate the tenancy and evict Miriam\nB. Torres and Adgar J.m. Banos (the \'Tenants\') and for an order to have the Tenants pay the rent\nthey owe because the Tenants failed to meet a condition specified in the order\nissued by the Board on March 22, 2021 with respect to application TNL- 27908-20.\n \nDeterminations:\n \n1.     The order provided that the Landlord could apply to\nthe Board under section 78 of the Residential Tenancies Act, 2006 (the\n\'Act\') without notice to the Tenants to terminate the tenancy and evict the Tenants if the Tenants\ndid not meet certain condition(s) specified in the order.\n \n2.     I find that the Tenants\nhave not met the following\nconditions specified in the order: The\nTenants did not pay $2,812.56 arrears on or before December 30, 2021. The\nTenants did not pay $2,216.93 rent on or before January 1, 2022.\n \n3.     The previous application included a request for an\norder for the payment of arrears of rent. The resulting order required the Tenants to pay rent or some or all of the arrears of rent. Accordingly, in addition to\neviction, the Landlord is entitled to request an order for the payment of arrears\nof rent and compensation.\n \n4.     The Tenants were ordered to pay $14,812.56 for rent\narrears and the costs related to the Landlord\'s application fee in Order TNL-27908-20. The amount that is still owing from that\norder is $4,162.56 and that amount is included in this order. As a result, the\nprevious order TNL-27908-20 is cancelled.\n \n5.     Since the date of the order, the Tenants have failed to pay the full rent that became owing.\n\n\n\n\n \n6.    \nThe Landlord collected a rent deposit\nof $2,141.93 from the\nTenants and this deposit is still being held by the Landlord.\n \n7.    \nInterest on the rent deposit is owing to the Tenants\nfor the period from October\n1, 2021 to February 3, 2022.\n \nIt is ordered that:\n \n1.     Order TNL-27908-20 is cancelled.\n \n2.     The tenancy between\nthe Landlord and the Tenants\nis terminated. The Tenants must move out of the rental unit on or\nbefore February 14, 2022.\n \n3.     The Tenants shall pay to the Landlord $4,583.59*.\n(Less any amounts paid since the application was filed on January 10, 2022.)\nThis amount represents the rent owing up to February 3, 2022 and the costs\nrelated to the application fee for the previous application, less the rent deposit and\ninterest the Landlord owes on the rent deposit.\n \n4.     The Tenants shall also pay to the Landlord $72.89 per day for compensation for the use of the unit starting February 4, 2022\nto the date the Tenants move out of the unit.\n \n5.     If the Tenants\ndo not pay the Landlord\nthe full amount\nowing* on or before February\n14, 2022, the Tenants will start to owe interest. This will be simple\ninterest calculated from February 15, 2022 at 2.00% annually on the balance\noutstanding.\n \n6.     If the unit is not vacated on or before\nFebruary 14, 2022, then starting\nFebruary 15, 2022, the Landlord may file this order\nwith the Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) so that the eviction may be\nenforced.\n \n7.     Upon receipt of this order,\nthe Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) is directed to give\nvacant possession of the unit to the Landlord on or after February 15, 2022.\n \n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n \nIan Speers\n\n\n\n\n \n\n\nFebruary 3, 2022 Date Issued\nVice Chair, Landlord and Tenant Board\n \nToronto North-RO\n47 Sheppard Avenue East,\nSuite 700, 7th Floor\nToronto ON M2N5X5\n \nThe tenant has until February 13, 2022\nto file a motion with the Board to set aside the order under\ns. 78(9) of the Act. If the tenant files the motion by February 13, 2022 the order will be stayed and the Board will schedule a hearing.\n \nIf you have any questions about\nthis order, call 416-645-8080 or toll free at 1-888-332-3234.\n\n\n\n\n \nIn accordance with section 81 of\nthe Act, the part of this order relating to the eviction expires on August 15, 2022 if the order has not been filed on or before this date with the Court Enforcement\nOffice (Sheriff) that has territorial jurisdiction where the rental unit is\nlocated.\n \n*           Refer to the attached Summary\nof Calculations.\n\n\n\n\nSummary of Calculations\nFile Number: TNL-36576-22\n \nAmount the Tenant must pay\n \n\n\n\nReason for amount\nowing\n\n\nPeriod\n\n\nAmount\n\n\n\n\n \nAmount owing\nfrom previous order\nor settlement plus New\n  Arrears and New NSF cheque charges and related administration charges\n\n\n \n$6,725.52\n\n\n\n\n \nLess the rent\n  deposit:\n\n\n \n\n\n \n-$2,141.93\n\n\n\n\n \nLess the interest owing on the rent deposit\n\n\n \nOctober 1, 2021\nto February 3,\n2022\n\n\n \n-$0.00\n\n\n\n\n \nPlus daily\ncompensation owing for\neach day of occupation\n  starting February 4, 2022\n\n\n \n$72.89\n(per day)\n\n\n\n\n \nTotal the Tenants must pay the Landlord:\n\n\n \n$4,583.59, + $72.89\nper day starting February\n  4, 2022', 'Metadata:\nDate:	2022-02-03\nFile number:	\nTNL-36576-22\n\nCitation:	Nubury Properties Limited v Banos, 2022 CanLII 122571 (ON LTB), <https://canlii.ca/t/jtp3j>, retrieved on 2023-05-16\nContent:\n\nOrder under Section 78(6)\nResidential Tenancies Act, 2006\n\