ears and the costs related to the Landlord\'s application fee in Order TNL-27908-20. The amount that is still owing from that order is $4,162.56 and that amount is included in this order. As a result, the previous order TNL-27908-20 is cancelled. 5.  Since the date of the order, the Tenants have failed to pay the full rent that became owing. 6. The Landlord collected a rent deposit of $2,141.93 from the Tenants and this deposit is still being held by the Landlord. 7. Interest on the rent deposit is owing to the Tenants for the period from October 1, 2021 to February 3, 2022. It is ordered that: 1.  Order TNL-27908-20 is cancelled. 2.  The tenancy between the Landlord and the Tenants is terminated. The Tenants must move out of the rental unit on or before February 14, 2022. 3.  The Tenants shall pay to the Landlord $4,583.59*. (Less any amounts paid since the application was filed on January 10, 2022.) This amount represents the rent owing up to February 3, 2022 and the costs related to the application fee for the previous application, less the rent deposit and interest the Landlord owes on the rent deposit. 4.  The Tenants shall also pay to the Landlord $72.89 per day for compensation for the use of the unit starting February 4, 2022 to the date the Tenants move out of the unit. 5.  If the Tenants do not pay the Landlord the full amount owing* on or before February 14, 2022, the Tenants will start to owe interest. This will be simple interest calculated from February 15, 2022 at 2.00% annually on the balance outstanding. 6.  If the unit is not vacated on or before February 14, 2022, then starting February 15, 2022, the Landlord may file this order with the Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) so that the eviction may be enforced. 7.  Upon receipt of this order, the Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) is directed to give vacant possession of the unit to the Landlord on or after February 15, 2022. Ian Speers February 3, 2022 Date Issued Vice Chair, Landlord and Tenant Board Toronto North-RO 47 Sheppard Avenue East, Suite 700, 7th Floor Toronto ON M2N5X5 The tenant has until February 13, 2022 to file a motion with the Board to set aside the order under s. 78(9) of the Act. If the tenant files the motion by February 13, 2022 the order will be stayed and the Board will schedule a hearing. If you have any questions about this order, call 416-645-8080 or toll free at 1-888-332-3234. In accordance with section 81 of the Act, the part of this order relating to the eviction expires on August 15, 2022 if the order has not been filed on or before this date with the Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) that has territorial jurisdiction where the rental unit is located. *    Refer to the attached Summary of Calculations. Summary of Calculations File Number: TNL-36576-22 Amount the Tenant must pay Reason for amount owing Period Amount Amount owing from previous order or settlement plus New Arrears and New NSF cheque charges and related administration charges $6,725.52 Less the rent deposit: -$2,141.93 Less the interest owing on the rent deposit October 1, 2021 to February 3, 2022 -$0.00 Plus daily compensation owing for each day of occupation starting February 4, 2022 $72.89 (per day) Total the Tenants must pay the Landlord: $4,583.59, + $72.89 per day starting February 4, 2022', 'Date: 2022-02-03 File number: TNL-36576-22  Citation: Nubury Properties Limited v Banos, 2022 CanLII 122571 (ON LTB), <https://canlii.ca/t/jtp3j>, retrieved on 2023-05-16', 'Order under Section 78(6) Residential Tenancies Act, 2006  File Number: TNL-36576-22      In the matter of:   1713, 377 RIDELLE AVENUE TORONTO ON M6B1K2        Between:   Nubury Properties Limited..   Landlord         and           Adgar J.m. Banos Miriam B. Torres   Tenants       On January 10, 2022, Nubury Properties Limited.. (the \'Landlord\') applied for an order to terminate the tenancy and evict Miriam B. Torres and Adgar J.m. Banos (the \'Tenants\') and for an order to have the Tenants pay the rent they owe because the Tenants failed to meet a condition specified in the order issued by the Board on March 22, 2021 with respect to application TNL- 27908-20.  Determinations:  1. The order provided that the Landlord could apply to the Board under section 78 of the Residential Tenancies Act, 2006 (the \'Act\') without notice to the Tenants to terminate the tenancy and evict the Tenants if the Tenants did not meet certain condition(s) specified in the order.  2. I find that the Tenants have not met the following conditions specified in the order: The Tenants did not pay $2,812.56 arrears on or before December 30, 2021. The Tenants did not pay $2,216.93 rent on or before January 1, 2022.  3. The previous application included a request for an order for the payment of arrears of rent. The resulting order required the Tenants to pay rent or some or all of the arrears of rent. Accordingly, in addition to eviction, the Landlord is entitled to request an order for the payment of arrears of rent and compensation.  4. The Tenants were ordered to pay $14,812.56 for rent arrears and the costs related to the Landlord\'s application fee in Order TNL-27908-20. The amount that is still owing from that order is $4,162.56 and that amount is included in this order. As a result, the previous order TNL-27908-20 is cancelled.  5. Since the date of the order, the Tenants have failed to pay the full rent that became owing.      6. The Landlord collected a rent deposit of $2,141.93 from the Tenants and this deposit is still being held by the Landlord.  7. Interest on the rent deposit is owing to the Tenants for the period from October 1, 2021 to February 3, 2022.  It is ordered that:  1. Order TNL-27908-20 is cancelled.  2. The tenancy between the Landlord and the Tenants is terminated. The Tenants must move out of the rental unit on or before February 14, 2022.  3. The Tenants shall pay to the Landlord $4,583.59*. (Less any amounts paid since the application was filed on January 10, 2022.) This amount represents the rent owing up to February 3, 2022 and the costs related to the application fee for the previous application, less the rent deposit and interest the Landlord owes on the rent deposit.  4. The Tenants shall also pay to the Landlord $72.89 per day for compensation for the use of the unit starting February 4, 2022 to the date the Tenants move out of the unit.  5. If the Tenants do not pay the Landlord the full amount owing* on or before February 14, 2022, the Tenants will start to owe interest. This will be simple interest calculated from February 15, 2022 at 2.00% annually on the balance outstanding.  6. If the unit is not vacated on or before February 14, 2022, then starting February 15, 2022, the Landlord may file this order with the Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) so that the eviction may be enforced.  7. Upon receipt of this order, the Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) is directed to give vacant possession of the unit to the Landlord on or after February 15, 2022.            Ian Speers        February 3, 2022 Date Issued Vice Chair, Landlord and Tenant Board  Toronto North-RO 47 Sheppard Avenue East, Suite 700, 7th Floor Toronto ON M2N5X5  The tenant has until February 13, 2022 to file a motion with the Board to set aside the order under s. 78(9) of the Act. If the tenant files the motion by February 13, 2022 the order will be stayed and the Board will schedule a hearing.  If you have any questions about this order, call 416-645-8080 or toll free at 1-888-332-3234.      In accordance with section 81 of the Act, the part of this order relating to the eviction expires on August 15, 2022 if the order has not been filed on or before this date with the Court Enforcement Office (Sheriff) that has territorial jurisdiction where the rental unit is located.  * Refer to the attached Summary of Calculations.     Summary of Calculations File Number: TNL-36576-22  Amount the Tenant must pay     Reason for amount owing   Period   Amount      Amount owing from previous order or settlement plus New Arrears and New NSF cheque charges and related administration charges    $6,725.52      Less the rent deposit:       -$2,141.93      Less the interest owing on the rent deposit    October 1, 2021 to February 3, 2022    -$0.00      Plus daily compensation owing for each day of occupation starting February 4, 2022    $72.89 (per day)      Total the Tenants must pay the Landlord:    $4,583.59, + $72.89 per day starting February 4, 2022', '377 Ridelle Avenue Tor To', '', 'December 30, 2021', '', 'February 3, 2022', '', '', '', '5. Since the date of the order, the Tenants have failed to pay the full rent that became owing.      6. The Landlord collected a rent deposit of $2,141.93 from the Tenants and this deposit is still being held by the Landlord.  7. Interest on the rent deposit is owing to the Tenants for the period from October 1, 2021 to February 3, 2022.  It is ordered that:  1. Order TNL-27908-20 is cancelled.  2. The tenancy between the Landlord and the Tenants is terminated. The Tenants must move out of the rental unit on or before February 14, 2022.  3. The Tenants shall pay to the Landlord $4,583.59*', '', 'No', '', 'No', '', 'Not stated', '', 'No', '', 'Not stated', '', 'No', '', 'Not stated', '', 'Not stated', '', 'Not stated', '', 'No', '', '0'),
