(49, 'TNL-36568-22', 'Asanza v Kamara, 2022 CanLII 122548 (ON LTB)', 'https://canlii.ca/t/jtp3c', 'English', 2022, 'Metadata:\nDate:	2022-02-04\nFile number:	\nTNL-36568-22\n\nCitation:	Asanza v Kamara, 2022 CanLII 122548 (ON LTB), <https://canlii.ca/t/jtp3c>, retrieved on 2023-05-16\nContent:\n\n\n\n \nOrder under Section 77\nResidential Tenancies Act, 2006\n \nFile Number: TNL-36568-22\n \n \n\n\n\nIn the matter\nof:\n\n\nBASEMENT RM #1, 17 TEDDER STREET NORTH YORK ON M6M4W9\n\n\n \n\n\n\n\nBetween:\n\n\nFernanda Asanza\n\n\nLandlord\n\n\n\n\n \n\n\n \nand\n\n\n \n\n\n\n\n \n\n\nMohamad Kamara\n\n\nTenant\n\n\n\n \n \n \nOn January 14, 2022, Fernanda Asanza (the \'Landlord\') applied for an order to terminate the tenancy and evict Mohamad Kamara (the\n\'Tenant\') because the Tenant entered into an agreement to terminate the\ntenancy.\n \nDeterminations:\n \n1.     The Landlord’s L3 application is brought under section 77 of the Residential Tenancies Act, 2006 (the “Act”).\n \n2.     Subsection 77(1) provides\nthe following two grounds on which a Landlord may apply\nunder section 77 of the Act:\n \n77 (1) A landlord\nmay, without notice to the tenant, apply to the Board for an order terminating a tenancy and evicting\nthe tenant if,\n \n(a)    \nthe landlord and tenant have entered\ninto an agreement to terminate\nthe tenancy; or\n \n(b)    \nthe tenant has given the landlord\nnotice of termination of the tenancy.\n \n3.    \nAnnexed to the Landlord’s application is a purported eviction\nnotice, given under section\n48 of the Act, dated December 6, 2021, purporting to terminate the tenancy\neffective noon on December 31, 2021. The\neviction notice is not on the prescribed N12 form to terminate a tenancy under\nsection 48 of the Act, and is also neither a notice of termination given by the\nTenant, nor an agreement to terminate the tenancy. It would appear that the notice also fails to identify the unit\nnumber of the rental unit. No other\nnotice or agreement forms part of the Landlord’s application.\n \n4.     The Landlord’s application does not disclose a ground\nto bring an application that complies with subsection 77(1) of the Act, as the purported notice of termination that\n\n\n\n\nFile Number: TNL-36568-22\n \nforms the basis of the application is a notice\ngiven by the Landlord, not a notice\ngiven by the Tenant. The application must therefore be dismissed.\n \nIt is ordered that:\n \n1.     The Landlord\'s application is dismissed.\n \n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n \nIan Speers\n\n\n\n\n \n\n\nFebruary 4, 2022 Date Issued\nVice Chair, Landlord\nand Tenant Board\n \nToronto North-RO\n47 Sheppard Avenue East,\nSuite 700, 7th Floor\nToronto ON M2N5X5\n \nIf you have any questions about\nthis order, call 416-645-8080 or toll free at 1-888-332-3234.', 'Metadata:\nDate:	2022-02-04\nFile number:	\nTNL-36568-22\n\nCitation:	Asanza v Kamara, 2022 CanLII 122548 (ON LTB), <https://canlii.ca/t/jtp3c>, retrieved on 2023-05-16\nContent:\n\nOrder under Section 77\nResidential Tenancies Act, 2006\n\nFile Number: TNL-36568-22\n\nIn the matter\nof:\n\nBASEMENT RM #1, 17 TEDDER STREET NORTH YORK ON M6M4W9\n\nBetween:\n\nFernanda Asanza\n\nLandlord\n\nand\n\nMohamad Kamara\n\nTenant\n\nOn January 14, 2022, Fernanda Asanza (the \'Landlord\') applied for an order to terminate the tenancy and evict Mohamad Kamara (the\n\'Tenant\') because the Tenant entered into an agreement to terminate the\ntenancy.\n\nDeterminations:\n\n1.     The Landlord’s L3 application is brought under section 77 of the Residential Tenancies Act, 2006 (the “Act”).\n\n2.     Subsection 77(1) provides\nthe following two grounds on which a Landlord may apply\nunder section 77 of the Act:\n\n77 (1) A landlord\nmay, without notice to the tenant, apply to the Board for an order terminating a tenancy and evicting\nthe tenant if,\n\n(a)    \nthe landlord and tenant have entered\ninto an agreement to terminate\nthe tenancy; or\n\n(b)    \nthe tenant has given the landlord\nnotice of termination of the tenancy.\n\n3.    \nAnnexed to the Landlord’s application is a purported eviction\nnotice, given under section\n48 of the Act, dated December 6, 2021, purporting to terminate the tenancy\neffective noon on December 31, 2021. The\neviction notice is not on the prescribed N12 form to terminate a tenancy under\nsection 48 of the Act, and is also neither a notice of termination given by the\nTenant, nor an agreement to terminate the tenancy. It would appear that the notice also fails to identify the unit\nnumber of the rental unit. No other\nnotice or agreement forms part of the Landlord’s application.\n\n4.     The Landlord’s application does not disclose a ground\nto bring an application that complies with subsection 77(1) of the Act, as the purported notice of termination that\n\nFile Number: TNL-36568-22\n\nforms the basis of the application is a notice\ngiven by the Landlord, not a notice\ngiven by the Tenant. The application must therefore be dismissed.\n\nIt is ordered that:\n\n1.     The Landlord\'s application is dismissed.\n\nIan Speers\n\nFebruary 4, 2022 Date Issued\nVice Chair, Landlord\nand Tenant Board\n\nToronto North-RO\n47 Sheppard Avenue East,\nSuite 700, 7th Floor\nToronto ON M2N5X5\n\nIf you have any questions about\nthis order, call 416-645-8080 or toll free at 1-888-332-3234.', 'Metadata:\nDate: 2022-02-04\nFile number:\nTNL-36568-22\nCitation: Asanza v Kamara, 2022 CanLII 122548 (ON LTB), <https://canlii.ca/t/jtp3c>, retrieved on 2023-05-16\nContent:\nOrder under Section 77\nResidential Tenancies Act, 2006\nFile Number: TNL-36568-22\nIn the matter\nof:\nBASEMENT RM #1, 17 TEDDER STREET NORTH YORK ON M6M4W9\nBetween:\nFernanda Asanza\nLandlord\nand\nMohamad Kamara\nTenant\nOn January 14, 2022, Fernanda Asanza (the \'Landlord\') applied for an order to terminate the tenancy and evict Mohamad Kamara (the\n\'Tenant\') because the Tenant entered into an agreement to terminate the\ntenancy.\nDeterminations:\n1.  The Landlord’s L3 appl