 Tenancies Act, 2006 File Number: TNL-36568-22 In the matter of: BASEMENT RM #1, 17 TEDDER STREET NORTH YORK ON M6M4W9 Between: Fernanda Asanza Landlord and Mohamad Kamara Tenant On January 14, 2022, Fernanda Asanza (the \'Landlord\') applied for an order to terminate the tenancy and evict Mohamad Kamara (the \'Tenant\') because the Tenant entered into an agreement to terminate the tenancy. Determinations: 1.  The Landlord’s L3 application is brought under section 77 of the Residential Tenancies Act, 2006 (the “Act”). 2.  Subsection 77(1) provides the following two grounds on which a Landlord may apply under section 77 of the Act: 77 (1) A landlord may, without notice to the tenant, apply to the Board for an order terminating a tenancy and evicting the tenant if, (a) the landlord and tenant have entered into an agreement to terminate the tenancy; or (b) the tenant has given the landlord notice of termination of the tenancy. 3. Annexed to the Landlord’s application is a purported eviction notice, given under section 48 of the Act, dated December 6, 2021, purporting to terminate the tenancy effective noon on December 31, 2021. The eviction notice is not on the prescribed N12 form to terminate a tenancy under section 48 of the Act, and is also neither a notice of termination given by the Tenant, nor an agreement to terminate the tenancy. It would appear that the notice also fails to identify the unit number of the rental unit. No other notice or agreement forms part of the Landlord’s application. 4.  The Landlord’s application does not disclose a ground to bring an application that complies with subsection 77(1) of the Act, as the purported notice of termination that File Number: TNL-36568-22 forms the basis of the application is a notice given by the Landlord, not a notice given by the Tenant. The application must therefore be dismissed. It is ordered that: 1.  The Landlord\'s application is dismissed. Ian Speers February 4, 2022 Date Issued Vice Chair, Landlord and T